@startuml 05_runtime_communication
title Runtime-Kommunikation — Sequenzdiagramm (Zug ausführen via WebUI)

skinparam sequence {
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #dfe6e9
  ParticipantBorderColor #2d3436
  ActorBackgroundColor #74b9ff
  LifeLineBorderColor #636e72
  ArrowColor #2d3436
  NoteBackgroundColor #fdcb6e
  NoteBorderColor #e17055
}

actor "Browser\n(WebUI)" as Browser #74b9ff
participant "Http4sRestApi\n:8080" as REST #55efc4
participant "GameController\n(Singleton)" as GC #fd79a8
participant "CommandParser" as CP #a29bfe
participant "MoveGenerator\n/ GameRules" as Model #dff9fb
participant "PassiveTrainer\n(AI Lernmodul)" as PT #dfe6e9
participant "Tui\n(Observer)" as TUI #ffeaa7

== Zug ausführen ==

Browser -> REST : POST /api/command\n{"command": "e2e4"}
activate REST

REST -> CP : parse("e2e4", appState)
activate CP
CP --> REST : Command.ApplyMove(Move(e2, e4))
deactivate CP

REST -> GC : eval(ApplyMove(Move(e2,e4)))
activate GC

GC -> GC : handleCommand(appState, cmd)
GC -> Model : MoveGenerator.legalMoves(state)
activate Model
Model --> GC : List[Move]
deactivate Model

GC -> Model : GameRules.applyMove(state, move)
activate Model
Model --> GC : newGameState
deactivate Model

GC -> Model : GameRules.computeStatus(newState)
activate Model
Model --> GC : GameStatus.Playing
deactivate Model

note right of GC
  appState wird atomar
  auf newAppState gesetzt
end note

GC -> GC : notifyObservers(newAppState)

GC ->> PT : PassiveTrainer.train(game, status)\n[nur bei Spielende, async]

GC -> REST : Observer.update(newAppState)
activate REST #f0f0f0
REST -> REST : currentState.set(newAppState)
deactivate REST

GC -> TUI : Observer.update(newAppState)
activate TUI
TUI -> TUI : renderFull() im Terminal
deactivate TUI

GC --> REST : newAppState
deactivate GC

REST --> Browser : HTTP 200 "Command dispatched"
deactivate REST

== Nächster Poll: State lesen ==

Browser -> REST : GET /api/state\n(alle 200ms)
activate REST
REST -> REST : currentState.get()
REST --> Browser : HTTP 200 GameStateResponse JSON\n{fen, status, highlights, ...}
deactivate REST

@enduml
